\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces IEE vs normalised entropy threshold $H_c/H_{\max }$ for M5 (Social Cascade) and M6 (ELAPSE ensemble) across ER, BA, and WS topologies at $n \in \{100, 200, 500\}$ ($N_{\mathrm  {test}}=10$ seeds per point). The inflection point marks the crossover centre $H_c^*$ separating subcritical (left; effective containment) and supercritical (right; bulk exposure) regimes. Crossover sharpness increases with algebraic connectivity $\lambda _2$: ER (high $\lambda _2$) shows the sharpest crossover; WS (low $\lambda _2$) shows the widest. Finite-size scaling indicates $H_c^*$ is size-dependent, consistent with a crossover rather than a universal phase transition.}}{27}{figure.caption.4}\protected@file@percent }
