\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Log-log plot of mean IEE vs network size $n \in \{50, 100, 200, 500, 1000\}$ (averaged over $N_{\mathrm  {test}}=20$ seeds per topology for $n \leq 500$; $N_{\mathrm  {test}}=10$ seeds for $n=1000$). Power-law fits (dashed lines) give exponents for M5: $\alpha _{\mathrm  {ER}} \approx 1.20$ and $\alpha _{\mathrm  {BA}} \approx 1.21$; for M6: $\alpha _{\mathrm  {ER}} \approx 1.04$ and $\alpha _{\mathrm  {BA}} \approx 1.22$. The $n=1000$ data points (rightmost, ER and BA only) confirm that scaling laws extend beyond the training range $n \leq 500$, with no super-linear entropy accumulation.}}{44}{figure.caption.19}\protected@file@percent }
