\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {10}{\ignorespaces Extended real-world validation: IEE for M0, M5, and M6 on four NetworkX real-world graphs (Karate Club $n=34$, Davis Southern Women $n=32$, Les Mis\'erables $n=77$, Florentine Families $n=15$). Error bars: 95\% CI over $N_{\mathrm  {test}}=10$ seeds. Red labels: M0/M5 reduction ratio. M5 consistently achieves $14$--$16\times $ IEE reduction; M6 (equal weights, no topology training) sits between M5 and M0. Consistent reduction across all four graph types confirms that entropy-gated deletion generalises beyond synthetic topologies.}}{59}{figure.caption.30}\protected@file@percent }
